The Phambili Secondary School teacher was apparently using the weapon to intimidate the children.  DURBAN - A Durban teacher has been suspended for pointing a gun at pupils. The KZN Education Department received numerous complaints from outraged parents. The Phambili Secondary School teacher was apparently using the weapon to intimidate the children. The department is investigating the incident. "Investigation is still ongoing, we are waiting for a preliminary report that will come out early next week," said Nkosinathi Ngcobo, Department of Education Head in KZN. "We don't have an issue whether its a toy gun or real gun, the fact that she's wielding a weapon on our learners is unacceptable, that's why we've put her on suspension. "We've put a timeline of 14 days, but the preliminary report must come as early as next week."